<a href='http://herbaria4.herb.berkeley.edu/eflora_display.php?tid=11347'><h3>View taxon page for Castilleja</h3></a><blockquote><h3></h3>
<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 0 ;"><a href="#YK1'">1.</a><a name="YK1."> </a> Inflorescence generally green, white, yellow, &plusmn; red-gray, bright pink, or &plusmn; purple, but not bright red; corolla 1&ndash;3 cm, beak generally &lt;= tube; generally bee-pollinated; lower corolla lip generally 3-pouched (except <I>Castilleja grisea</I>, <I>Castilleja plagiotoma</I>), teeth generally &plusmn; erect, white or green to purple-red

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#YK2'">2.</a><a name="YK2."> </a> Perennial herb to subshrub

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#YK3'">3.</a><a name="YK3."> </a> Herbage gray-green, except bract lobes and calyx white-woolly; calyx divided deeper on sides than abaxially and adaxially <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18283">.....&nbsp;C. plagiotoma</a> (2)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#YK3.">3'</a><a name="YK3'"> </a> Herbage, including bract lobes and calyx, gray-green to densely white-woolly; calyx divided deeper abaxially and adaxially than on sides, or divided &plusmn; equally

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#YK4'">4.</a><a name="YK4."> </a> Calyx divided much deeper abaxially and adaxially than on sides

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#YK5'">5.</a><a name="YK5."> </a> Hairs stellate; San Clemente Island <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18212">.....&nbsp;C. grisea</a> (2)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#YK5.">5'</a><a name="YK5'"> </a> Hairs simple or branched; Klamath Ranges, High Cascade Range, High Sierra Nevada, San Bernardino Mountains, Great Basin Floristic Province

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#YK6'">6.</a><a name="YK6."> </a> Herbage glandular; corolla 16&ndash;20 mm, lower lip 5&ndash;7 mm, teeth &plusmn; green-white or &plusmn; purple, &plusmn; triangular; stem generally unbranched; bract lobes &plusmn; acute <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18229">.....&nbsp;C. lemmonii</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#YK6.">6'</a><a name="YK6'"> </a> Herbage stiff-hairy, nonglandular; corolla 13&ndash;16 mm, lower lip 2 mm, teeth dark green, incurved; stem much-branched; bract lobes truncate or rounded <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18285">.....&nbsp;C. praeterita</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#YK4.">4'</a><a name="YK4'"> </a> Calyx divided &plusmn; equally

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#YK7'">7.</a><a name="YK7."> </a> Herbage &plusmn; white-woolly

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#YK8'">8.</a><a name="YK8."> </a> Plant 8&ndash;30 cm; leaves 20&ndash;60 mm; hairs simple; Klamath Ranges, High North Coast Ranges, High Cascade Range, n High Sierra Nevada, Modoc Plateau <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18171">.....&nbsp;C. arachnoidea</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#YK8.">8'</a><a name="YK8'"> </a> Plant 8&ndash;15 cm; leaves 5&ndash;20 mm; hairs branched; Klamath Ranges <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18310">.....&nbsp;C. schizotricha</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#YK7.">7'</a><a name="YK7'"> </a> Herbage puberulent to coarsely hairy

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#YK9'">9.</a><a name="YK9."> </a> Herbage ashy-puberulent; bract tips dusty red, &plusmn; purple, or green-yellow; hairs dense, partitioned, much-branched; seed coat walls irregularly netted &mdash; seed coat tight-fitting; San Bernardino Mountains <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18186">.....&nbsp;C. cinerea</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#YK9.">9'</a><a name="YK9'"> </a> Herbage not ashy-puberulent; bract tips generally yellow-green or &plusmn; purple; hairs &plusmn; stiff, &plusmn; unbranched; seed coat walls with ladder-like thickenings

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 42 ;"><a href="#YK10'">10.</a><a name="YK10."> </a> Bract lobes acuminate, green-margined; seed coat loose-fitting <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18260">.....&nbsp;C. nana</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 42 ;"><a href="#YK10.">10'</a><a name="YK10'"> </a> Bract lobes generally truncate or rounded (acute), white-margined; seed coat tight-fitting <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18279">.....&nbsp;C. pilosa</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#YK2.">2'</a><a name="YK2'"> </a> Annual

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#YK11'">11.</a><a name="YK11."> </a> Bracts green throughout

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#YK12'">12.</a><a name="YK12."> </a> Leaves and bracts entire <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18179">.....&nbsp;C. campestris</a>

